>/hmofa/ mods that add a story or sidequest or otherwise give the waifur some personality?
Not really /hmofa/ since there's no romance per se, but Legend of Mana (at least the ps1 original, don't know anything about the remaster) features two strong waifur candidates, one of which you team up with on multiple occasions during certain questline (Daena) while the other one (Sierra) just shows up twice (I think) as boss encounter on another questline. Both have quite a bit of personality to them, especially Daena, given that she has both more screen time and a more prominent role in her subplot. After finishing certain characters' questlines they become available as travelling companions anytime, so you can share your adventures with them. I guess you could just fantasize about your own /hmofa/ ventures with them, since imagination is the first and often the best source to cultivate one's magical realm anyway. As for vidya with waifur-ish characters in general, let me dig through my external memory for anything that may be less mentioned
>Bunny Hunter
Didn't play it (yet?), try if you can stomach rpgmaker graphics. /hmofa/
>FF9
Dragonrat party member.
>Tail Concerto
Canine princess and feline bandit leader.
>Planet Laika
Mane charicter. This is a weird one, humans become canine anthros because reasons, so she's still technically human, I guess.
>Solatorobo
Didn't play any of these but the characters seem cute.
>Amorous
Renamon cosplayer. /hmofa/ if you make yourself a human male avatar
>Date a mink
>Date an otter
Short and sweet vns but not much content. /hmofa/
>Blind date game/generator
>Love at First Tail
As above but unfinished.
>Space Paws
It's okay. /hmofa/
>Metal Wolf Chaos XD
I look back fondly at the time spent with (or rather inside) Metal Wolf-chan.

This is painful, /hmofa/ enjoyers sure could use a lot more pandering in media, as opposed to kemonomimi trash fans. Even finding satisfying /m/ vidya outside of Armored Core is (very) much easier.
